<div id="review_1355555999" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1355555999" />
    <a title="Ellen Taylor" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3340440-ellen-taylor"><img alt="Ellen Taylor" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1320621748p2/3340440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1355555999?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ellen Taylor" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ellen Taylor" href="/user/show/3340440-ellen-taylor">Ellen Taylor</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781634132121" href="/book/show/23974760-the-widow-or-widower-next-door">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1355555999" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14014022616670957080">This collection of responses to questions of how widows and widowers gave some rather predictable advice on shoulds and should nots when it comes to interacting with those in deep grief. I read this to find ways to help those friends who have lost their spouses or children and hope I have a better idea of how to be a good listener and include those who are suffering from loneliness or isolation during their grief journey. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


