        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1184951365" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14665031726413527370">*** I received this book from the author in exchange for an honest review. ***<br/><br/>I haven&apos;t experienced such a big loss yet, so when I picked up this book I did not think it would struck me this much.<br/>I had to stop at some point because of the pain I was feeling in my chest - we do not think about these things as much as we should (or at least I know I don&apos;t). Being an ordinary 20 year old death is not on top of my agenda but it is something I will eventually have to face and this book helped me prep</span>
  <span id="freeText14665031726413527370" style="display:none">*** I received this book from the author in exchange for an honest review. ***<br /><br />I haven't experienced such a big loss yet, so when I picked up this book I did not think it would struck me this much.<br />I had to stop at some point because of the pain I was feeling in my chest - we do not think about these things as much as we should (or at least I know I don't). Being an ordinary 20 year old death is not on top of my agenda but it is something I will eventually have to face and this book helped me preparing for it.<br />Death is inevitable and unpredictable, so as much we try to not think about it, to tell ourselves that "It won't be us" (as a song really close to me says)... it will happen. It's life.<br />Reading <i>The Widow or Widower Next Door </i> encouraged me to spend more time with my loved ones and create memories with them, because when the time comes memories are what we are left with. Let's make some good ones.<br /><br />Grief is of course another strong topic in this book and since everyone reacts differently, the only thing we can do is stay close to anyone who goes through such an important loss.<br />I always thought grown ups were stronger and that was why most of the time they would look completely fine even after life events like this. Truth is that they may get used to being alone, but it will still hurt even after many years. I learned that grief takes time.<br /><br />This is a hinghly moving and touching book. It keeps each chapter/topic very simple so it is accessible to everybody.<br /><br />PS. The cover is not casual, it is absolutely perfect. It made my heart melt and cry at the same time.</span>
